WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.984 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.984 --> 00:00:02.460 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.460 --> 00:00:11.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.810 --> 00:00:14.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:16.710 align:middle line:84%
And joining me today
is Dr. Baskaran Pillai.

00:00:16.710 --> 00:00:17.950 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.950 --> 00:00:20.940 align:middle line:84%
He's a spiritual scientist,
an academic scholar,

00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:23.310 align:middle line:84%
and a world thought
leader who's been featured

00:00:23.310 --> 00:00:25.700 align:middle line:84%
in Time magazine for
his deep commitment

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:28.490 align:middle line:84%
to helping people
across the globe

00:00:28.490 --> 00:00:31.310 align:middle line:84%
realize their full
human potential.

00:00:31.310 --> 00:00:33.360 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Pillai is an
enlightened master.

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:36.080 align:middle line:84%
He's from the South
Indian Siddha tradition,

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:38.145 align:middle line:84%
which is an unbroken
ancient lineage

00:00:38.145 --> 00:00:39.830 align:middle line:90%
of spiritual scientists.

00:00:39.830 --> 00:00:43.350 align:middle line:84%
And they've reached the
pinnacle of human evolution.

00:00:43.350 --> 00:00:43.850 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:45.170 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for being here.

00:00:45.170 --> 00:00:45.990 align:middle line:84%
>>BASKARAN PILLAI:
I'm delighted.

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:46.906 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, I am, too.

00:00:46.906 --> 00:00:49.345 align:middle line:84%
I'm excited about what
we can talk about here.

00:00:49.345 --> 00:00:50.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:50.390 --> 00:00:52.620 align:middle line:84%
So first of all,
tell me a little bit

00:00:52.620 --> 00:00:55.170 align:middle line:84%
about your upbringing
and where you grew up,

00:00:55.170 --> 00:00:58.050 align:middle line:84%
and how you got involved
with the Siddha tradition.

00:00:58.050 --> 00:00:59.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:59.390 --> 00:01:02.795 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: So I was born in
an island in southern India.

00:01:02.795 --> 00:01:07.630 align:middle line:90%


00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:11.580 align:middle line:84%
When I grew up, in that
island, that island is known

00:01:11.580 --> 00:01:17.340 align:middle line:84%
for its special quality,
which is, all over the world,

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:22.340 align:middle line:84%
people come to the island
for removing their karma.

00:01:22.340 --> 00:01:23.670 align:middle line:90%


00:01:23.670 --> 00:01:28.230 align:middle line:84%
There are some 27 wells in
the island, in the temple.

00:01:28.230 --> 00:01:29.380 align:middle line:90%


00:01:29.380 --> 00:01:35.960 align:middle line:84%
They're called a temple--
the waters in the well

00:01:35.960 --> 00:01:38.530 align:middle line:90%
are capable of removing karma.

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:39.155 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:01:39.155 --> 00:01:40.370 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yeah.

00:01:40.370 --> 00:01:45.303 align:middle line:84%
So I grew up in a
background of spirituality.

00:01:45.303 --> 00:01:48.430 align:middle line:90%


00:01:48.430 --> 00:01:53.920 align:middle line:84%
But I did not know all
of it until I grew up.

00:01:53.920 --> 00:01:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was your family a
family of spiritual healers?

00:01:56.800 --> 00:01:58.330 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yes, yes, yes.

00:01:58.330 --> 00:02:01.990 align:middle line:84%
My family lived
close to the temple,

00:02:01.990 --> 00:02:05.890 align:middle line:84%
and my brother was an
officer in the temple.

00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:09.000 align:middle line:84%
And he was in charge of
the sanctum santorum.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:12.652 align:middle line:84%
So we have a spiritual
background as a family.

00:02:12.652 --> 00:02:13.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A long lineage of it.

00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:15.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:02:15.050 --> 00:02:17.830 align:middle line:84%
And would you see people go
in and out of the temple?

00:02:17.830 --> 00:02:20.040 align:middle line:84%
What was your
perspective as a child?

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:22.610 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: As a child,
I did not know much.

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:26.610 align:middle line:84%
But then, although I was
very attracted to the Buddha,

00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:29.040 align:middle line:90%
even when I was very young.

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:32.560 align:middle line:84%
Although the Buddha was
a renegade and never

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:35.410 align:middle line:84%
conformed to
Hinduism, because he

00:02:35.410 --> 00:02:37.550 align:middle line:84%
believed that there
was no God, no soul.

00:02:37.550 --> 00:02:38.810 align:middle line:90%


00:02:38.810 --> 00:02:43.130 align:middle line:84%
That was very revolutionary for
him to do it in sixth century

00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:46.640 align:middle line:84%
BC, which is 600
years before Christ,

00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:49.870 align:middle line:84%
he said there was
no God and no soul

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:54.090 align:middle line:84%
All that you need to do
is to experience nirvana,

00:02:54.090 --> 00:02:56.330 align:middle line:90%
which is emptiness of the mind.

00:02:56.330 --> 00:02:58.300 align:middle line:90%
So I was attracted to that.

00:02:58.300 --> 00:03:04.660 align:middle line:84%
So even as a boy, I used to have
a small picture of the Buddha

00:03:04.660 --> 00:03:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and would go and meditate before
him, not knowing too much.

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:14.440 align:middle line:84%
But what attracted me was his
concept of non-violence, which

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:17.550 align:middle line:84%
Jainism and things like that,
you should not harm anyone.

00:03:17.550 --> 00:03:18.650 align:middle line:90%


00:03:18.650 --> 00:03:21.380 align:middle line:90%
And that's how we started out.

00:03:21.380 --> 00:03:24.400 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not knowing too many
things about the Buddha.

00:03:24.400 --> 00:03:26.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Without reading
extensively, but feeling

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:27.737 align:middle line:90%
the essence.

00:03:27.737 --> 00:03:29.570 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: Feeling the
essence of meditation.

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:30.794 align:middle line:90%
So I was doing that.

00:03:30.794 --> 00:03:31.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: When you very young?

00:03:31.960 --> 00:03:32.907 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Very young.

00:03:32.907 --> 00:03:34.310 align:middle line:90%


00:03:34.310 --> 00:03:38.030 align:middle line:84%
Then later on, and
I went to college

00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:42.550 align:middle line:84%
and did some studies
in Buddhist literature.

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:43.850 align:middle line:90%


00:03:43.850 --> 00:03:47.070 align:middle line:84%
I studied all of
Shakespeare's plays.

00:03:47.070 --> 00:03:52.750 align:middle line:84%
And I just really wanted
to go and teach in England.

00:03:52.750 --> 00:03:57.995 align:middle line:84%
And these were my aspirations,
never knowing my future.

00:03:57.995 --> 00:03:59.640 align:middle line:90%


00:03:59.640 --> 00:04:02.445 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What's the link between
Shakespeare and the Buddha?

00:04:02.445 --> 00:04:05.630 align:middle line:90%


00:04:05.630 --> 00:04:10.340 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: I just was
interested in literature.

00:04:10.340 --> 00:04:15.380 align:middle line:90%
And later on, I do not know.

00:04:15.380 --> 00:04:18.850 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there was
something in my soul

00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:20.680 align:middle line:84%
that attracted me
to Shakespeare.

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:25.270 align:middle line:84%
Somebody has done some research
on myself and Shakespeare.

00:04:25.270 --> 00:04:27.051 align:middle line:90%
And it has been published.

00:04:27.051 --> 00:04:27.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:04:27.550 --> 00:04:29.845 align:middle line:84%
Because I find Shakespeare
very spiritual.

00:04:29.845 --> 00:04:30.720 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yeah, yeah.

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:31.270 align:middle line:90%
He was.

00:04:31.270 --> 00:04:32.811 align:middle line:84%
It was absolutely
very spiritual man.

00:04:32.811 --> 00:04:34.560 align:middle line:90%


00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:35.940 align:middle line:90%
There's no doubt about it.

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:37.315 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No, his
works have lasted

00:04:37.315 --> 00:04:39.774 align:middle line:90%
for centuries for a reason.

00:04:39.774 --> 00:04:41.690 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: Because the
last play of Shakespeare

00:04:41.690 --> 00:04:45.370 align:middle line:84%
is "The Tempest," where he talks
about the whole world is maya.

00:04:45.370 --> 00:04:47.182 align:middle line:90%


00:04:47.182 --> 00:04:48.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: He's very
psychological, as well.

00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:49.686 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yeah.

00:04:49.686 --> 00:04:51.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And was there
a strong emphasis

00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:52.710 align:middle line:90%
on education in your family?

00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:53.460 align:middle line:90%
Of going to study?

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:54.751 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Of course, of course.

00:04:54.751 --> 00:04:55.365 align:middle line:90%
Definitely.

00:04:55.365 --> 00:04:56.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:04:56.640 --> 00:04:59.650 align:middle line:84%
And so you carried that
on and you went to school.

00:04:59.650 --> 00:05:02.730 align:middle line:84%
And how did-- was the
tradition of the Siddha someone

00:05:02.730 --> 00:05:04.590 align:middle line:90%
that you-- that inspired you?

00:05:04.590 --> 00:05:06.890 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: I came to the
Siddha tradition later on.

00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:09.975 align:middle line:84%
I started with
the Beatles' guru.

00:05:09.975 --> 00:05:11.440 align:middle line:90%


00:05:11.440 --> 00:05:17.340 align:middle line:84%
So after my bachelor's
in British literature,

00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:20.610 align:middle line:84%
I just joined-- even
after my master's.

00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:23.090 align:middle line:84%
I have a master's in
American literature, too.

00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:27.670 align:middle line:84%
So after that, I was attracted
to the Beatles' guru.

00:05:27.670 --> 00:05:28.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Whose name was?

00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:30.313 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.

00:05:30.313 --> 00:05:30.930 align:middle line:90%


00:05:30.930 --> 00:05:33.930 align:middle line:84%
Who is the founder of the
transcendental mediation

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:34.490 align:middle line:90%
program.

00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:35.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How did you meet him?

00:05:35.930 --> 00:05:39.600 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: Well, he-- after
he established himself

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:41.670 align:middle line:84%
in the West, he
came back to India.

00:05:41.670 --> 00:05:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And he was teaching
in India through many

00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:45.065 align:middle line:90%
of his Western disciples.

00:05:45.065 --> 00:05:46.180 align:middle line:90%


00:05:46.180 --> 00:05:48.590 align:middle line:84%
And I was attracted
to his teachings,

00:05:48.590 --> 00:05:51.820 align:middle line:84%
particularly because
he was explaining

00:05:51.820 --> 00:05:53.200 align:middle line:90%
everything in a scientific way.

00:05:53.200 --> 00:05:56.050 align:middle line:90%
And I have a scientific mind.

00:05:56.050 --> 00:06:00.610 align:middle line:84%
So I was attracted to the
teachings, especially when he

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:07.630 align:middle line:84%
proved that medication can
improve your understanding

00:06:07.630 --> 00:06:08.720 align:middle line:90%
and change your brain.

00:06:08.720 --> 00:06:09.830 align:middle line:90%


00:06:09.830 --> 00:06:11.300 align:middle line:90%
So that attracted me.

00:06:11.300 --> 00:06:12.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are you
interested in that

00:06:12.990 --> 00:06:15.190 align:middle line:84%
from the neurochemical
perspective

00:06:15.190 --> 00:06:16.931 align:middle line:84%
or from the spiritual
perspective?

00:06:16.931 --> 00:06:17.556 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Both.

00:06:17.556 --> 00:06:18.032 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or both?

00:06:18.032 --> 00:06:18.532 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:18.532 --> 00:06:19.700 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Both.

00:06:19.700 --> 00:06:24.110 align:middle line:84%
I wanted proof, because I wanted
to contemporize my teachings.

00:06:24.110 --> 00:06:26.370 align:middle line:84%
Because unless you use
the contemporary language,

00:06:26.370 --> 00:06:28.440 align:middle line:90%
people won't understand it.

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:30.950 align:middle line:84%
Because they want
proof for everything.

00:06:30.950 --> 00:06:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And that also helps
to understand,

00:06:33.470 --> 00:06:38.460 align:middle line:84%
in a more precise and
deeper way, meditation.

00:06:38.460 --> 00:06:42.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when a guru
teaches meditation,

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:45.470 align:middle line:84%
and when you get
into those teachings

00:06:45.470 --> 00:06:49.720 align:middle line:84%
and you experience that
state of bliss and nirvana,

00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:51.050 align:middle line:90%
what happens in the brain?

00:06:51.050 --> 00:06:52.770 align:middle line:90%


00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: Well,
the-- in the brain--

00:06:56.280 --> 00:07:00.840 align:middle line:84%
so when we are now talking
to each other, the brain,

00:07:00.840 --> 00:07:03.020 align:middle line:90%
the frontal lobe is very active.

00:07:03.020 --> 00:07:07.140 align:middle line:84%
Because that is where you
have the knowledge that you

00:07:07.140 --> 00:07:11.020 align:middle line:84%
are Lisa for instance,
and I am who I am.

00:07:11.020 --> 00:07:13.700 align:middle line:84%
All this information
is in the frontal lobe.

00:07:13.700 --> 00:07:14.870 align:middle line:90%


00:07:14.870 --> 00:07:18.502 align:middle line:84%
So that is what gives
us our ego identity.

00:07:18.502 --> 00:07:19.085 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:07:19.085 --> 00:07:20.290 align:middle line:90%


00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:23.610 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: And then if you go a
little above the parietal lobe,

00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:27.280 align:middle line:84%
it also gives an understanding
of where you are,

00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:29.810 align:middle line:84%
which place you are
sitting, all these things.

00:07:29.810 --> 00:07:31.585 align:middle line:90%
But these things will recede.

00:07:31.585 --> 00:07:32.425 align:middle line:90%


00:07:32.425 --> 00:07:34.050 align:middle line:84%
Then they will have
no identity at all.

00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:35.150 align:middle line:90%


00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:36.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In meditation.

00:07:36.100 --> 00:07:36.725 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yeah.

00:07:36.725 --> 00:07:38.367 align:middle line:84%
You can go to that
state in meditation.

00:07:38.367 --> 00:07:38.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:07:38.950 --> 00:07:41.925 align:middle line:84%
Where you actually let
go of the egoic mind.

00:07:41.925 --> 00:07:42.800 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Completely.

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:43.300 align:middle line:90%
Completely.

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:45.850 align:middle line:84%
And it usually takes about
two hours to do that.

00:07:45.850 --> 00:07:47.610 align:middle line:90%


00:07:47.610 --> 00:07:50.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In the beginning,
when you are sitting,

00:07:50.700 --> 00:07:54.100 align:middle line:84%
how do you-- and I'm sure you've
done this for so long-- how do

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:58.550 align:middle line:84%
you start to eliminate
and wash away the ego?

00:07:58.550 --> 00:08:03.615 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: You just start with
examining what is happening.

00:08:03.615 --> 00:08:05.820 align:middle line:90%


00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.920 align:middle line:84%
The thoughts are
coming to your mind.

00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:08.729 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:08:08.729 --> 00:08:11.020 align:middle line:84%
And then you don't identify
yourself with the thoughts,

00:08:11.020 --> 00:08:12.195 align:middle line:90%
and you watch the thoughts.

00:08:12.195 --> 00:08:13.390 align:middle line:90%


00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And then, the thoughts
do not belong to you.

00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:20.189 align:middle line:84%
There's a famous saying
in Tibetan Buddhism:

00:08:20.189 --> 00:08:21.230 align:middle line:90%
thoughts are your guests.

00:08:21.230 --> 00:08:22.810 align:middle line:90%


00:08:22.810 --> 00:08:24.290 align:middle line:90%
They check in and check out.

00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:25.340 align:middle line:90%


00:08:25.340 --> 00:08:26.360 align:middle line:90%
You are the host.

00:08:26.360 --> 00:08:28.140 align:middle line:90%


00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:30.880 align:middle line:84%
Your real self is the gap
in between the two thoughts.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:32.820 align:middle line:90%


00:08:32.820 --> 00:08:35.330 align:middle line:84%
There is a gap in
between the two thoughts.

00:08:35.330 --> 00:08:40.372 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to meditate,
the gaps will keep increasing.

00:08:40.372 --> 00:08:41.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It gets bigger.

00:08:41.330 --> 00:08:42.900 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: And then
there comes a time

00:08:42.900 --> 00:08:46.920 align:middle line:84%
when you do not know who
you are, or you're thinking

00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:48.890 align:middle line:84%
thoughts, and the
mind disappears.

00:08:48.890 --> 00:08:53.470 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, you can
get into your higher self.

00:08:53.470 --> 00:08:56.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: When you
have the thoughts

00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.470 align:middle line:84%
and they attach to the
ego, does that mean

00:08:58.470 --> 00:08:59.650 align:middle line:90%
that the gap is not there?

00:08:59.650 --> 00:09:01.251 align:middle line:90%
That there is no gap, right?

00:09:01.251 --> 00:09:03.500 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: When there is a
gap, there is no experience.

00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:05.740 align:middle line:90%
There is no experience at all.

00:09:05.740 --> 00:09:07.454 align:middle line:84%
Momentarily, there
won't be experience.

00:09:07.454 --> 00:09:08.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's no judgment.

00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:09.911 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: No judgment, nothing.

00:09:09.911 --> 00:09:10.840 align:middle line:90%
You do not know.

00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:12.450 align:middle line:90%
It is an out of body experience.

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:14.120 align:middle line:90%
Or out of mind experience.

00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:15.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:17.645 align:middle line:84%
>>PILLAI: It is something
like you are sleeping.

00:09:17.645 --> 00:09:19.590 align:middle line:90%


00:09:19.590 --> 00:09:22.322 align:middle line:84%
And everybody has some
experience of of it

00:09:22.322 --> 00:09:23.390 align:middle line:90%
during sleep.

00:09:23.390 --> 00:09:25.580 align:middle line:84%
Because during sleep,
the mind disappears.

00:09:25.580 --> 00:09:28.900 align:middle line:84%
But then what happens is,
there's no awareness in sleep.

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:29.920 align:middle line:90%
You lose everything.

