reflects only that reality.

00:22:51.140 --> 00:22:55.790 align:middle line:84%
So you have to change your
inner consciousness in order

00:22:55.790 --> 00:22:57.382 align:middle line:90%
to see something outside.

00:22:57.382 --> 00:22:58.840 align:middle line:84%
That's why that
gives a lot of hope

00:22:58.840 --> 00:23:02.960 align:middle line:84%
for people who are people
who have no skills,

00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:05.260 align:middle line:90%
for instance, no education.

00:23:05.260 --> 00:23:07.170 align:middle line:90%
Can they succeed?

00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:09.890 align:middle line:90%
Yes, they can succeed in life.

00:23:09.890 --> 00:23:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And your country, in
India, where you see poverty

00:23:13.170 --> 00:23:14.250 align:middle line:90%
lining the streets.

00:23:14.250 --> 00:23:15.170 align:middle line:90%
In many countries.

00:23:15.170 --> 00:23:17.740 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: 2,000 years ago.

00:23:17.740 --> 00:23:20.110 align:middle line:84%
It's not that India
is poor only today.

00:23:20.110 --> 00:23:22.990 align:middle line:90%
2000 years ago it was poor.

00:23:22.990 --> 00:23:25.820 align:middle line:84%
They asked the Siddha--
it has been translated

00:23:25.820 --> 00:23:28.200 align:middle line:84%
in all the languages
of the world.

00:23:28.200 --> 00:23:29.680 align:middle line:90%
His name is Thiruvalluvar.

00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:32.670 align:middle line:90%
He lived 2000 years from today.

00:23:32.670 --> 00:23:36.738 align:middle line:84%
They asked him why there are
so many people poor here.

00:23:36.738 --> 00:23:38.930 align:middle line:90%


00:23:38.930 --> 00:23:44.370 align:middle line:90%
And he said, [SPEAKING TAMIL]

00:23:44.370 --> 00:23:47.870 align:middle line:84%
This is in my language, and
this is the Siddha's language.

00:23:47.870 --> 00:23:50.810 align:middle line:84%
He said there are so
many people who are poor.

00:23:50.810 --> 00:23:54.500 align:middle line:84%
It is because they don't
know how to intend.

00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:56.120 align:middle line:90%


00:23:56.120 --> 00:23:58.780 align:middle line:90%
Intention is important.

00:23:58.780 --> 00:24:00.955 align:middle line:84%
Their intention is
focused on poverty.

00:24:00.955 --> 00:24:03.530 align:middle line:90%


00:24:03.530 --> 00:24:05.950 align:middle line:84%
If they can change
their intention,

00:24:05.950 --> 00:24:07.570 align:middle line:84%
then they can see
the other reality.

00:24:07.570 --> 00:24:08.640 align:middle line:90%


00:24:08.640 --> 00:24:11.870 align:middle line:84%
If this moment you are
poor, and then you continue,

00:24:11.870 --> 00:24:14.710 align:middle line:84%
he says, to be in it
forever, and thinking

00:24:14.710 --> 00:24:15.990 align:middle line:90%
that I have no hope.

00:24:15.990 --> 00:24:17.930 align:middle line:90%
You play this victim more.

00:24:17.930 --> 00:24:21.430 align:middle line:84%
But that is not the case, then
you can change your reality

00:24:21.430 --> 00:24:24.000 align:middle line:84%
and then intend
something very beautiful.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:25.910 align:middle line:90%
Then that will be the reality.

00:24:25.910 --> 00:24:29.150 align:middle line:84%
So that, he says,
in 2000 years ago,

00:24:29.150 --> 00:24:33.990 align:middle line:84%
he was saying people don't
know how to use their mind.

00:24:33.990 --> 00:24:38.030 align:middle line:84%
How the intention is
really what matters.

00:24:38.030 --> 00:24:41.270 align:middle line:84%
You know, Wayne Dyer also
has a book on intention.

00:24:41.270 --> 00:24:45.030 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
know how to intend.

00:24:45.030 --> 00:24:48.570 align:middle line:84%
The intention creates
the material reality.

00:24:48.570 --> 00:24:50.367 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And Wayne is
a student of yours.

00:24:50.367 --> 00:24:50.950 align:middle line:90%
>>PILLAI: Yes.

00:24:50.950 --> 00:24:55.550 align:middle line:84%
And he has been my-- I
